answer.en:
### Entity vs Value Object

Entities have a unique identity that persists over time, while Value Objects are defined by their attributes and are immutable. Use Entities for concepts that need lifecycle tracking, and Value Objects for concepts that only matter for their values.

```typescript
class User { // Entity - has identity
  id: UUID;
  name: string;
}

class Money { // Value Object - immutable
  constructor(amount: number, currency: string) {}
  equals(other: Money): boolean {
    return this.amount === other.amount && this.currency === other.currency;
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Forgetting that Value Objects must be immutable and comparable by value, not identity.

answer.ru:
