### Bounded Context

A Bounded Context is an explicit boundary within which a domain model applies consistently. It isolates different models and their ubiquitous languages, preventing confusion when the same term means different things in different parts of the system.

```typescript
// Shipping Context
class Order {
  id: OrderId;
  status: 'pending' | 'shipped';
}

// Billing Context
class Order {
  id: OrderId;
  totalPrice: Money;
  paymentStatus: 'unpaid' | 'paid';
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing Bounded Context with microservices—contexts are logical, services are deployment boundaries.

