### Aggregate and Aggregate Root

An Aggregate is a cluster of associated entities and value objects treated as a single unit. The Aggregate Root is the entry point that maintains invariants and ensures all operations within the aggregate preserve consistency rules.

```typescript
class Order { // Aggregate Root
  private items: OrderItem[] = [];

  addItem(product: Product, quantity: number): void {
    if (this.items.length >= MAX_ITEMS) throw new Error('Too many items');
    this.items.push(new OrderItem(product, quantity));
  }
}

class OrderItem { // Part of aggregate, not directly accessible
  constructor(product: Product, quantity: number) {}
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Allowing external code to modify aggregate members directly, breaking encapsulation and invariants.

