### Domain Events

Domain Events represent significant things that happen in the domain and are published by aggregates. They enable aggregates to communicate without direct dependencies, allowing other parts of the system to react asynchronously.

```typescript
class Order { // Aggregate Root
  private events: DomainEvent[] = [];

  createOrder(items: OrderItem[]): void {
    this.items = items;
    this.events.push(new OrderCreatedEvent(this.id, items));
  }

  getDomainEvents(): DomainEvent[] { return this.events; }
}

class SendConfirmationEmailService {
  handle(event: OrderCreatedEvent): void {
    sendEmail(event.customerId, 'Your order confirmed');
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Storing domain events in the aggregate but never publishing them to interested subscribers—events must be handled outside.

answer.ru:
