### Anti-Corruption Layer Implementation

An Anti-Corruption Layer (ACL) is a boundary that translates between your rich domain model and external systems' anemic models. It prevents external complexity from leaking into your core domain by adapting incoming and outgoing data.

```typescript
interface LegacyUserDTO {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

class UserACL {
  toDomain(legacyUser: LegacyUserDTO): User {
    return new User(legacyUser.id, legacyUser.name, legacyUser.email);
  }
  toExternal(domainUser: User): LegacyUserDTO {
    return { id: domainUser.id, name: domainUser.name, email: domainUser.email };
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing ACL with simple DTO mapping—ACL must protect domain integrity and handle incompatibilities, not just transform data.

answer.ru:
