### Payment Processing Bounded Context

Define aggregates (Payment, Refund) with explicit business rules as value objects. Use domain events (PaymentProcessedEvent, PaymentFailedEvent) to communicate state changes. Implement compensating transactions through a saga pattern or compensating event handler to rollback failed payments atomically.

```typescript
class PaymentAggregate {
  constructor(private id: string, private amount: Money) {}

  process(): PaymentEvent[] {
    if (!this.canProcess()) throw new PaymentError();
    return [new PaymentProcessedEvent(this.id, this.amount)];
  }

  refund(): RefundEvent[] {
    return [new RefundInitiatedEvent(this.id, this.amount)];
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Ignoring failure scenarios—payments must be idempotent and support compensation/rollback.

